#ArduiPi_OLED : operation program 
#KeyMotion : main program

### because of symbolic links issue, these steps are needed to run program #############
#
# 1. copy and paste onto hardware (not on USB directory)
# 2. unzip libroyale-3.17.0.56-LINUX-arm-32Bit.zip
# 3. open folder libroyale-3.17.0.56-LINUX-arm-32Bit/bin/
# 4. copy libroyale.so, libroyaleCAPI.so files. 
#    (These files should be link files - arrow mark on file image)
# 5. paste and overwrite into this folder KeyMotion/bin/
# 
#### compile ArduiPi_OLED####
#
# 6. open folder ArduiPi_OLED/ and type in terminal : sudo make
# 7. open folder ArduiPi_OLED/example and type in terminal : sudo make
#
#### compile KeyMotion   #### 
#
# 8. open folder KeyMotion/source/ and type : sudo cmake .
# 9. open folder KeyMotion/source/cpp/KeyMotion/KeyMotion_v2c/ and type : sudo make
#
#### bash files ####
#
# In bash files, directory needs to be modified ( open.sh, program.sh, systemDown.sh )
# If it is necessary to run the program "first_page" directly when linux turns on,
# please refer to this : 
#
# raspberrypi.stackexchange.com/questions/12730/start-a-lxterminal-on-startup
# 
# there needs some setup to run the program automatically.
#
